00:25:46.691 --> 00:25:48.730
But I feel like I had
good intentions, right?

00:25:48.730 --> 00:25:54.110
[LAUGH] On the fourth
one here, the paradigm

00:25:54.110 --> 00:25:57.800
of the headman or
headwoman is working

00:25:57.800 --> 00:25:59.540
on governing agreements.

00:25:59.540 --> 00:26:03.520
And again, I have the story
of Google and Larry Page

00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:06.010
here as just setting the
tone at the beginning

00:26:06.010 --> 00:26:10.830
of the book about how it is
you can go public and actually

00:26:10.830 --> 00:26:12.250
improve democracy
and capitalism.

00:26:13.497 --> 00:26:15.830
Do you tell that story when
you hire people or interview

00:26:15.830 --> 00:26:16.329
people?

00:26:17.280 --> 00:26:21.085
It's a phenomenal story about
how you decide to go public.

00:26:22.120 --> 00:26:25.280
Only 16 companies had actually
done the Dutch auction

00:26:25.280 --> 00:26:28.260
in the US that Google
did before Google did it.

00:26:28.260 --> 00:26:30.764
Now that number is about
that number every year,

00:26:30.764 --> 00:26:32.180
but people are
still afraid of it.

00:26:32.180 --> 00:26:34.400
They don't understand
how it could work.

00:26:34.400 --> 00:26:36.752
So what happened
is that you take

00:26:36.752 --> 00:26:38.210
an agreement which
we already have.

00:26:38.210 --> 00:26:40.626
Larry didn't say, let's change
all the laws and the rules.

00:26:40.626 --> 00:26:42.360
He said, let's
use what we've got

00:26:42.360 --> 00:26:44.240
and let's make it all change.

00:26:44.240 --> 00:26:46.800
The same thing happened
with the broadband,

00:26:46.800 --> 00:26:52.130
with the analog, when Google bid
on something in order to-- I'm

00:26:52.130 --> 00:26:54.860
told that the reason we
can keep our phone numbers

00:26:54.860 --> 00:26:57.080
is because of what
Google did with the SEC.

00:26:58.200 --> 00:26:59.450
And that story is in the book.

00:27:01.210 --> 00:27:03.049
So you take the
governing agreements

00:27:03.049 --> 00:27:05.340
that already exist-- because
it's really hard to change

00:27:05.340 --> 00:27:07.240
government, even through voting.

00:27:08.700 --> 00:27:10.485
We vote, and we
think, didn't we vote

00:27:10.485 --> 00:27:13.032
for different people who
would work on different stuff?

00:27:13.032 --> 00:27:14.240
And we don't always get them.

00:27:14.240 --> 00:27:17.140
So you have to learn to work
the governing agreement.

00:27:17.140 --> 00:27:20.630
So this book has stories of
people who are doing that.

00:27:20.630 --> 00:27:24.510
So I gave new names to these.

00:27:24.510 --> 00:27:27.650
So instead of warrior, clown,
hunter, headman, I said,

00:27:27.650 --> 00:27:29.540
what are they working on?

00:27:29.540 --> 00:27:33.420
And it turns out what the
warrior is working on is really

00:27:33.420 --> 00:27:36.256
this seeing reality in a
way that we normally don't.

00:27:36.256 --> 00:27:37.880
And I've got a couple
of stories there.

00:27:37.880 --> 00:27:39.380
But the one story
I want to tell you

00:27:39.380 --> 00:27:42.440
is the reconnection
entrepreneur.

00:27:42.440 --> 00:27:45.840
Kip Baratoff-- oh.

00:27:45.840 --> 00:27:48.020
Kip is quite an
amazing young man.

00:27:48.020 --> 00:27:50.700
And he decided that the social
system he wanted to change

00:27:50.700 --> 00:27:54.000
was how economic
development happened along

00:27:54.000 --> 00:27:55.790
the coast of Oregon,
where he lives.

00:27:57.050 --> 00:27:59.680
The fishermen were going out
of business left and right

00:27:59.680 --> 00:28:00.324
who were there.

00:28:00.324 --> 00:28:02.490
All of the people that
supported them were going out

00:28:02.490 --> 00:28:02.990
of business.

00:28:02.990 --> 00:28:04.450
They were creating
social systems

00:28:04.450 --> 00:28:06.510
to give them money to
try and retrain them.

00:28:06.510 --> 00:28:08.930
Let's let you be something
else besides a fisherman.

00:28:08.930 --> 00:28:11.860
Let's let you be something else
besides a company that cans.

00:28:11.860 --> 00:28:14.180
Let's just move all of you
out of that and change it.

00:28:14.180 --> 00:28:16.194
And he said, but that
is a way to live.

00:28:16.194 --> 00:28:17.860
And on the coast,
it's really important.

00:28:18.940 --> 00:28:21.202
He created a cooperative.

00:28:21.202 --> 00:28:22.410
It's not a legal cooperative.

00:28:22.410 --> 00:28:28.740
Be but he brought together the
boat, the captain that fishes,

00:28:28.740 --> 00:28:31.080
the fisher people who are
on the boat-- in fact,

00:28:31.080 --> 00:28:35.640
the company's called Fish
People-- the people who can

00:28:35.640 --> 00:28:37.940
and process, those
who distribute,

00:28:37.940 --> 00:28:40.170
and those who sell
it, like Costco,

00:28:40.170 --> 00:28:45.380
into an ongoing group that
meets together every other week

00:28:45.380 --> 00:28:46.710
to look at the whole system.

00:28:47.960 --> 00:28:49.880
When you go to Costco,
you can actually

00:28:49.880 --> 00:28:52.710
learn what they're doing with
any specific piece of fish.

00:28:52.710 --> 00:28:55.400
Any of you shop at Costco ever?

00:28:55.400 --> 00:28:57.496
So take your phone.

00:28:57.496 --> 00:28:59.120
It will look for Fish
People's package.

00:28:59.120 --> 00:29:00.480
You will see a QR code on it.

00:29:00.480 --> 00:29:03.420
It will you who the captain of
the boat was that caught that.

00:29:03.420 --> 00:29:05.910
It'll tell you who it
was that canned it.

00:29:05.910 --> 00:29:07.440
It'll tell you how
it was processed.

00:29:07.440 --> 00:29:10.090
It will even tell you what the
mercury and any other metals

00:29:10.090 --> 00:29:12.720
content is in that piece of
fish you're about to buy.

00:29:12.720 --> 00:29:15.310
It has creating chaos in
Costco, because everybody

00:29:15.310 --> 00:29:18.950
wants to know why is nobody else
doing what's happening here?

00:29:18.950 --> 00:29:21.390
And it's rebuilding the
entire economic development

00:29:21.390 --> 00:29:23.910
structure around the
fishing industry,

00:29:23.910 --> 00:29:26.460
rather than trying to solve the
problem, which was retraining

00:29:26.460 --> 00:29:28.605
them, giving them money
to get them through.

00:29:29.620 --> 00:29:32.410
And they're figuring out how
to do sustainable fishing.

00:29:33.787 --> 00:29:35.870
I don't think we have
Google buying from them yet,

00:29:35.870 --> 00:29:38.357
but it just occurred to me,
we should talk about them.

